habitat: On south-facing scree slope. In a Trans Pecos: Volcanic Rockland, mostly granite. Plant associations include: Fouquieria splendens, Parthenium incanum, Aloysia wrightii, Viguiera stenoloba, Bouteloua gracilis, Astrolepis sinuata, Cheilanthes sp., Opuntia engelmanii var. engelmanii, Yucca faxoniana, and Opuntia imbricata var. arborescens.
locality: Hudspeth County.

habitat: On south-facing slope located in a Trans-Pecos: steppe and Desert Grassland community. In shallow rocky soil, over granite. Plant associations include: Fouquieria splendens, Parthenium incanum, Aloysia wrightii, Viguiera stenoloba, Bouteloua gracilis, Astrolepis sinuata, Astrolepis cochisensis, Cheilanthes sp., Opuntia engelmannii var. engelmannii, Yucca faxoniana, and Opuntia imbricata var. arborescens.
locality: Hudspeth County.

habitat: In a Trans-Pecos: Montane Mesic and Canyon Woodland. Dominant in a narrow canyon at high elevation on shallow soil over granite. Plant associations include: Rhus virens var. virens, Garrya ovata ssp. goldmanii, Rhus virens, Lonicera albiflora, Ruellia sp., Aristida purpurea var. nealleyi, and Yucca baccata.
locality: Hudspeth County.

habitat: On high elevation west facing slope. Located on Trans-Pecos: Mixed Desert and Thornscrub community. Substrate comprised of shallow soil over rhyolite. Plant associations include: Acacia greggii var. greffii, Parthenium incanum, Krameria grayi, Bouteloua eriopoda, Bouteloua gracilis, Yucca faxoniana, Opuntia imbricata var. arborescens, and Dasylirion leiophyllum.
locality: Hudspeth County.

habitat: In Trans-Pecos: Montane Mesic and Canyon Hardwood Forest community. Specimen on rocky canyon bottom, with both limestone and granite formations evident. Plant associations include: Quercus grisea, Juniperus monsperma, Acacia greggii var. greggii, Rhus microphylla, Fallugia paradoxa, Leptochloa dubia, Botriochloa laguroides, Muhlenbergia emersleyi, and Opuntia imbricata var. arborescens.
locality: Hudspeth County.
